@startuml
title Email login and session creation - sequence diagram

actor User
participant "WebFrontend" as FE
participant "Auth HTTP API" as AuthApi
participant "AuthService" as Auth
participant "Community UserService" as Community
database "MongoDB" as Mongo
database "Redis" as Redis

User -> FE : enters email
FE -> AuthApi : POST /email/login/start(email)
AuthApi -> Auth : start_email_login(email)
Auth -> Redis : store login code / challenge
AuthApi --> FE : 200 code sent

User -> FE : enters code
FE -> AuthApi : POST /email/login/finish(code)
AuthApi -> Auth : finish_email_login(code)
Auth -> Redis : validate code
Auth -> Community : GetUserByEmail(email)
Community -> Mongo : find user

alt user not found
  Community --> Auth : NOT_FOUND
  Auth -> Community : CreateUser(email)
  Community -> Mongo : insert user
  Community --> Auth : UserResponse
else user exists
  Community --> Auth : UserResponse
end

Auth -> Redis : set sid:<signed_sid> = Session(user)
AuthApi --> FE : AuthResponse + Set-Cookie sid
FE -> AuthApi : GET /me
AuthApi -> Redis : get sid session
AuthApi --> FE : authenticated user

@enduml
